---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - TaxPortal" description="TaxPortal terms of service outlining the terms and conditions for using our tax calculators and tools.">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-canvas dark:bg-primary">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-8 dark:text-on-primary">Terms of Service</h1>
      <div class="prose max-w-none space-y-6 text-body dark:text-muted">
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> July 2026</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing and using TaxPortal ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">2. Service Description</h2>
        <p>TaxPortal provides free, browser-based tax calculators, educational guides, and informational resources for various countries and tax types. Our tools are designed for estimation and informational purposes only.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">3. Disclaimer of Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>THE CALCULATORS AND CONTENT ON TAXPORTAL ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. TaxPortal does not provide tax, legal, or financial advice. The results produced by our calculators are estimates and should not be relied upon as the sole basis for tax filing decisions. Always consult a qualified tax professional for advice specific to your situation.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">4. Accuracy and Updates</h2>
        <p>We strive to keep our calculators and content updated with the latest tax laws and rates. However, we do not guarantee that all information is always current or error-free. Tax laws change frequently, and users are responsible for verifying the accuracy of tax rules before making financial decisions.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">5. No Guarantee of Results</h2>
        <p>TaxPortal makes no guarantee that the results from our calculators will match the tax liability calculated by any tax authority. Actual tax owed may differ based on individual circumstances, additional deductions, credits, or changes in tax law.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">6. User Responsibility</h2>
        <p>You are solely responsible for ensuring the accuracy of the information you enter into our calculators and for the decisions you make based on the results provided.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, TaxPortal shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising from the use of our services.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to this page.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms of Service, contact us at support@taxportal.com.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>